          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConvertOverpunch4",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a specific type of numeric encoding known as overpunch. Overpunch encoding is a method used in mainframe systems to store numeric values with implied decimal points and sign information within a single character. This function specifically handles a 4-character overpunch encoded string, converting it into a standard numeric format."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
